name: Halls Fish & Chips
reviews:

Food was always very good and staff were pleasant and cheerful. What a difference recently when we called on a Saturday lunch time to find the cafe completely empty. A girl came through to take our order, she didn't speak and seemed that it was a chore to serve. We both had fish and chips. Chips were fine but the fish was very poor quality as was the batter. I hope that this was a one off but judging by the empty cafe I don't think it was. We were the only people in the whole time we were there. I thought l had only been given chips.  Opened them up to see tiny piece of fish.
Will not waste my money going here again.  If they think a sprat for fish is acceptable.   They need to see what decent chip shops provide. I was very disappointed!

The fish was very small which I get everything has become more expensive. However the fish didn't taste very fresh, it was VERY fishy tasting and chips were overly greasy! I had 1 bite of the fish and couldn't touch it anymore.

Sadly the staff who served me were not very welcoming, didn't say hello and just glared the whole time.
